# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Spark — environment configuration
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Spark is BYOK by default: users paste their own DeepSeek key in
# Settings → API key, and that key is encrypted on their device. The web
# build works with zero env vars set.
#
# The two vars below are optional and only useful in specific deployments.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and uncomment what you need.

# ── DEEPSEEK_API_KEY (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set this only if you're hosting a *shared* Spark deployment where the
# server provides a fallback key for users who haven't pasted their own.
# Most self-hosters do NOT need this.
#
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here

# ── DEEPSEEK_API_URL (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Override only if you're proxying DeepSeek behind your own gateway.
# Defaults to https://api.deepseek.com/v1
#
# DEEPSEEK_API_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/v1

# ── NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL (recommended for production) ───────────────────────
# Used as the canonical URL and metadataBase for OpenGraph, Twitter cards,
# and JSON-LD. Defaults to https://get-spark.app
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://get-spark.app
